==Legacy==
A sequel, ''[[Last Ninja 3]]'' was released in 1991.

The ''Last Ninja Remix'' re-release version has an added short intro sequence, minor graphic changes and a remixed soundtrack. 

The Limited Edition of the original release included a ninja mask and a rubber shuriken (not available with the Remix versions of the game).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/showmag.cgi?mag=C+VG/Issue081/Pages/CVG08100021.jpg |title=Archive - Magazine viewer |publisher=World of Spectrum |access-date=2012-07-30}}</ref>

In 2015 the [[source code]] of the [[Konix]] version was discovered.<ref>[http://www.retrocollect.com/News/last-ninja-2-port-discovered-for-unreleased-konix-multisystem-console.html Last Ninja 2 Port Discovered For Unreleased Konix Multisystem Console] on retrocollect.com (19 January 2015)</ref><ref>[http://www.konixmultisystem.co.uk/index.php?id=news LAST NINJA 2 Konix Multisystem game and source found] on konixmultisystem.co.uk (17 January 2015)</ref>

